e-shaped hairs at tips of male cheliceral apophyses. Scale lines: 10 µm (66–69), 100 µm (64–65)." captionText-3="FIGURES 70–75. Hoplopholcus minotaurinus Senglet, 1971 (CJVK 2267). 70. Embolar sclerite with sperm duct opening (arrow). 30. Hair-like processes on embolar sclerite. 72. Male gonopore with epiandrous spigots. 73. Epigynum. 74–75. Male and female ALS. Scale lines: 10 µm (74), 20 µm (70, 75), 30 µm (71), 100 µm (72), 200 µm (73)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613136" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613138" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613140" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613142" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3613136/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3613138/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3613140/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/3613142/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 47–75</figureCitation>
